frog-marched out of the White House

976
01:12:43,914 --> 01:12:47,147
in handcuffs.
And believe me, when I use that name,

977
01:12:47,147 --> 01:12:48,607
I measure my words.

978
01:12:56,636 --> 01:12:58,618
- Mr. Wilson!
- Excuse me.

979
01:12:58,618 --> 01:13:00,390
We came all the way from Portland
for this.

980
01:13:00,390 --> 01:13:01,642
Hello. Okay.

981
01:13:02,372 --> 01:13:05,604
My wife and I have never sought publicity,

982
01:13:06,439 --> 01:13:08,837
but I know when I tell her about
all of the support out here today,

983
01:13:08,733 --> 01:13:10,714
she'll be thrilled and humbled.

984
01:13:15,615 --> 01:13:17,909
- Hello?
- Valerie, turn on MSNBC.

985
01:13:17,909 --> 01:13:19,473
Mom, why can't I have
some juice?

986
01:13:19,473 --> 01:13:20,725
Okay. Hold on one second.

987
01:13:20,725 --> 01:13:22,289
They've launched an investigation.

988
01:13:23,332 --> 01:13:25,000
Ashcroft just announced it.

989
01:13:24,896 --> 01:13:26,669
They say he's going to convene
a grand jury.

990
01:13:26,669 --> 01:13:28,337
Hold on a second.

991
01:13:28,441 --> 01:13:32,195
The FBI now is conducting
a criminal investigation

992
01:13:32,091 --> 01:13:35,532
into who leaked the name
of the CIA undercover operative...

993
01:13:35,637 --> 01:13:37,826
I'm going to be back later.
I've got to go over to Fox.

994
01:13:37,826 --> 01:13:39,808
They want me to comment
on the investigation.

995
01:13:39,808 --> 01:13:42,832
- Joe, just hold on.
- Valerie, we've got to fight this.

996
01:13:42,936 --> 01:13:44,500
We cannot... We've got to push back.

997
01:13:44,605 --> 01:13:46,690
Mom! Where's my doll?

998
01:13:48,150 --> 01:13:49,193
I've got another call. I gotta go.

999
01:13:49,193 --> 01:13:50,653
Joe! You have to...

1000
01:13:52,947 --> 01:13:54,094
Joe Wilson.

1001
01:13:54,094 --> 01:13:57,952
Joe, it's Chris Matthews.
I just spoke to Karl Rove.

1002
01:13:57,848 --> 01:14:01,393
He told me, "Wilson's wife is fair game."

1003
01:14:11,613 --> 01:14:13,803
Thank you for coming here.

1004
01:14:14,220 --> 01:14:17,452
I wanted to convey my outrage to you
in person.

1005
01:14:18,182 --> 01:14:19,955
I know it's not easy, but I want you to know

1006
01:14:20,059 --> 01:14:23,709
how much the Agency appreciates
your silence in the light of this matter.

1007
01:14:24,543 --> 01:14:28,506
We can't afford
to have this knife fight go on any longer.

1008
01:14:30,383 --> 01:14:32,156
I get death threats every day.

1009
01:14:32,260 --> 01:14:34,867
People threaten to kill my husband,
hurt my children.

1010
01:14:35,493 --> 01:14:36,535
I went to the Agency

1011
01:14:36,640 --> 01:14:39,142
and I requested security
to protect my family.

1012
01:14:39,768 --> 01:14:44,460
I was declined because, "My circumstances
fall outside budget protocols."

1013
01:14:45,712 --> 01:14:49,883
If this is a knife fight, sir,
right now we're fighting it alone.

1014
01:14:52,594 --> 01:14:55,097
Joe Wilson versus the White House, huh?

1015
01:14:54,993 --> 01:14:57,600
Well, all I can say is good luck.

1016
01:14:57,495 --> 01:15:00,207
But I feel, as a friend, I should tell you

1017
01:15:00,207 --> 01:15:03,961
that those men, those few men
in that building over there,

1018
01:15:04,065 --> 01:15:07,610
are the most powerful men
in the history of the world.

1019
01:15:07,610 --> 01:15:12,303
How much of a stretch do you think it'd be
for them to take on Joe Wilson?

1020
01:15:13,763 --> 01:15:16,891
Joe is out there on his own, Valerie,

1021
01:15:16,787 --> 01:15:18,664
but I know we can trust you.

1022
01:15:19,602 --> 01:15:21,479
Speak to your husband.

1023
01:15:27,319 --> 01:15:31,490
Tucker Carlson says,
"Wilson's wife sent him on a boondoggle."

1024
01:15:31,386 --> 01:15:33,367
Says, "He needed the work."

1025
01:15:33,576 --> 01:15:35,036
Who needs to work for free?

1026
01:15:35,348 --> 01:15:39,520
It's not like Niger is renowned
for its fine dining and celebrated operas.

1027
01:15:40,145 --> 01:15:42,127
It reminds me of Paris.

1028
01:15:44,838 --> 01:15:48,905
Listen. Someone from Vanity Fair called,
they want to do a piece.

1029
01:15:48,800 --> 01:15:52,346
They want to do a full-scale interview,
photographs.

1030
01:15:52,346 --> 01:15:54,223
Tell the whole story.

1031
01:15:54,223 --> 01:15:56,517
What do you think about that?

1032
01:15:57,247 --> 01:15:58,915
What do I think?

1033
01:16:00,897 --> 01:16:04,546
Do I want my photograph in Vanity Fair?
Is that the question?

1034
01:16:04,964 --> 01:16:06,632
Valerie, this is our chance.

1035
01:16:06,945 --> 01:16:10,073
- To do what?
- To tell our side of the story.

1036
01:16:10,282 --> 01:16:14,036
It'll mean a dozen,
maybe 50 TV appearances.

1037
01:16:14,036 --> 01:16:15,391
We have to do that.

1038
01:16:15,391 --> 01:16:18,103
They're killing us on Fox, in the blogs.

1039
01:16:18,103 --> 01:16:20,710
They're drowning us out.
We've got to strike back.

1040
01:16:23,838 --> 01:16:26,028
What? What's wrong? What did I say?

1041
01:16:26,132 --> 01:16:29,990
Don't you get it, Joe?
I mean, where does all of this stop?

1042
01:16:31,867 --> 01:16:33,640
Our address is on the Internet.

1043
01:16:33,536 --> 01:16:35,622
A photo of our house.

1044
01:16:35,726 --> 01:16:38,333
I've changed our phone number, what,
five times now?

1045
01:16:38,333 --> 01:16:42,608
My name... My name is everywhere!
My real name, Joe!

1046
01:16:42,504 --> 01:16:46,154
Where does all of this tough-talk
and publicity and noise,

1047
01:16:46,049 --> 01:16:48,761
and all of this bullshit that you're doing,
where does it get us?

1048
01:16:48,865 --> 01:16:52,515
- Where?
- Andy Card told the Financial Times

1049
01:16:52,619 --> 01:16:57,520
that they are rolling earthmovers
over Joe Wilson."Earthmovers."

1050
01:16:57,520 --> 01:17:00,857
Well, I'm sorry,
you're not going to get me without a fight.

1051
01:17:00,753 --> 01:17:03,047
Not without one hell of a fight.

1052
01:17:02,943 --> 01:17:05,862
It's the White House, Joe.
It's the White House.

1053
01:17:05,862 --> 01:17:08,574
Do you seriously think you can pick a fight
with the White House and win?

1054
01:17:08,574 --> 01:17:10,972
- They'll bury us!
- They'll bury us if we don't!

1055
01:17:10,868 --> 01:17:12,745
- Joe.
- Listen to me, Valerie.

1056
01:17:12,745 --> 01:17:16,290
- No, no, you listen to me!
- Valerie! Valerie! Valerie!

1057
01:17:16,603 --> 01:17:19,314
Does that make me right
if I shout louder than you?

1058
01:17:19,627 --> 01:17:21,921
If I shout louder than you, am I right?

1059
01:17:21,921 --> 01:17:26,301
If I'm the White House
and I shout a million times louder than you,

1060
01:17:26,197 --> 01:17:27,865
does that make me right?

1061
01:17:27,865 --> 01:17:29,951
They lied, Valerie.

1062
01:17:29,951 --> 01:17:32,141
They lied. That's the truth.

1063
01:17:33,183 --> 01:17:34,956
Truth. Right.

1064
01:17:35,999 --> 01:17:38,502
Well, by the time they're finished with us,

1065
01:17:38,502 --> 01:17:40,587
- we won't know what that is.
- Mom!

1066
01:17:43,194 --> 01:17:44,445
Great.

1067
01:17:59,879 --> 01:18:01,339
Look, Mommy.

1068
01:18:05,614 --> 01:18:07,282
Is Scooter home?

1069
01:18:14,999 --> 01:18:18,232
- What's that?
- The Senate just finished its investigation.

1070
01:18:18,023 --> 01:18:21,673
The findings of the Select Committee
on Intelligence, all 511 pages.

1071
01:18:22,507 --> 01:18:24,176
Check out page 39.

1072
01:18:30,849 --> 01:18:32,831
- Hi, Daddy!
- Who's the prettiest?

1073
01:18:32,831 --> 01:18:35,333
Hey there, monster. How are you?

1074
01:18:36,272 --> 01:18:39,922
Go get there.
Get some play in before it starts to rain.

1075
01:18:41,277 --> 01:18:42,424
What's that?

1076
01:18:42,320 --> 01:18:45,657
That's the Senate Select Committee
Intelligence report.

1077
01:18:46,804 --> 01:18:48,577
On page 39,

1078
01:18:48,577 --> 01:18:52,539
it says, "The former ambassador's wife
offered up his name."

1079
01:18:52,852 --> 01:18:55,772
It then includes a memorandum
written by Valerie Plame

1080
01:18:55,668 --> 01:18:59,735
which says, "My husband has
good relations with both the Prime Minister

1081
01:18:59,839 --> 01:19:01,403
"and the former Minister of Mines,

1082
01:19:01,403 --> 01:19:04,010
"both of whom could shed light
on this sort of activity."

1083
01:19:04,010 --> 01:19:06,408
- This is exactly what I've been denying.
- No. No.

1084
01:19:06,408 --> 01:19:09,433
I've been to every newspaper,
every television, radio,

1085
01:19:09,328 --> 01:19:10,997
anybody that would listen to me,

1086
01:19:10,997 --> 01:19:13,604
saying my wife did not send me on a junket.

1087
01:19:13,604 --> 01:19:16,315
- I didn't send you. I didn't have that power.
- You sent an e-mail.

1088
01:19:16,211 --> 01:19:17,775
The SSCI found the e-mail.

1089
01:19:17,879 --> 01:19:19,965
- I write hundreds of e-mails.
- Why didn't you tell me?

1090
01:19:19,860 --> 01:19:22,467
It never occurred to you, in all this time,
that this would be important?

1091
01:19:22,467 --> 01:19:25,491
I didn't make the decision.
I was asked to write a recommendation.

1092
01:19:25,491 --> 01:19:28,411
What was I supposed to do?
Not say my husband knows about this?

1093
01:19:28,516 --> 01:19:30,914
Well, they have this now.

1094
01:19:30,810 --> 01:19:33,625
They'll call me a liar and it will stick.

1095
01:19:33,625 --> 01:19:36,858
'Cause they have all the power.
What do I have? My word.

1096
01:19:37,692 --> 01:19:39,465
You've got to speak up, Valerie.

1097
01:19:39,569 --> 01:19:43,636
You've got to go on the record now.
You've got to defend us. Now.

1098
01:19:46,139 --> 01:19:47,703
So what do you want me to do?

1099
01:19:47,703 --> 01:19:51,561
Go to the papers like you did?
Write a piece in The New York Times?

1100
01:19:51,561 --> 01:19:52,917
You know I'd have to submit it
to the Agency...

1101
01:19:52,917 --> 01:19:54,272
- Daddy!
- Wait, wait, wait.

1102
01:19:54,272 --> 01:19:55,941
Honey, go play. Go on, go on.

1103
01:19:56,045 --> 01:19:57,505
The Agency?

1104
01:19:57,505 --> 01:20:00,738
Valerie, who's your loyalty to?
To your husband or the CIA?

1105
01:20:00,738 --> 01:20:04,179
It's to my family.
I put my family first, always.

1106
01:20:04,179 --> 01:20:07,099
Were you putting them first
when you wrote that goddamn article?

1107
01:20:08,141 --> 01:20:09,497
Mommy!

1108
01:20:10,123 --> 01:20:11,478
Trevor?

1109
01:20:12,417 --> 01:20:14,085
Go find Samantha.

1110
01:20:15,128 --> 01:20:18,361
I'm taking different routes
to and from school.

1111
01:20:18,361 --> 01:20:22,949
I'm looking in empty rooms,
under beds, every time I come home.

1112
01:20:22,740 --> 01:20:24,305
A home we're going to lose pretty soon

1113
01:20:24,305 --> 01:20:27,746
because your work has dried up
and your clients are running for cover.

1114
01:20:27,746 --> 01:20:30,144
What has all this achieved, Joe?

1115
01:20:35,775 --> 01:20:37,548
Maybe you're right.

1116
01:20:39,008 --> 01:20:42,032
Maybe I just should
have kept my mouth shut.

1117
01:20:42,449 --> 01:20:45,473
Is that what your dad taught you, Valerie?

1118
01:20:45,786 --> 01:20:47,559
Is that what Colonel Sam Plame would say?

1119
01:20:47,663 --> 01:20:49,331
A good American
just keeps his mouth shut.

1120
01:20:49,331 --> 01:20:52,251
A good American just looks the other way?

1121
01:20:53,294 --> 01:20:55,380
Did you send me to Niger?

1122
01:20:55,692 --> 01:20:57,987
His business is struggling,
he's on the slide.

1123
01:20:57,987 --> 01:21:00,281
I'll pull a few strings,
send the old man a bone.

1124
01:21:00,281 --> 01:21:02,783
- Is that pretty much what happened?
- How dare you.

1125
01:21:02,783 --> 01:21:04,452
Did you send me?

1126
01:21:04,973 --> 01:21:06,850
You think I'm lying to you.

1127
01:21:06,850 --> 01:21:08,623
Could I tell if you were?

1128
01:21:14,671 --> 01:21:16,340
Trevor? Honey?

1129
01:21:22,701 --> 01:21:25,412
Come on, Sam. Let's get in the car.

1130
01:21:26,455 --> 01:21:28,749
- Bye, guys! I'll see you at home.
- Bye, Daddy!

1131
01:21:28,749 --> 01:21:30,000
Bye!

1132
01:21:30,000 --> 01:21:32,086
I'm taking my car, okay?

1133
01:21:33,441 --> 01:21:36,361
Joe Wilson was a shameless self-promoter.

1134
01:21:36,257 --> 01:21:40,324
Everything about his story was either a lie
or a hoax or he was incompetent.

1135
01:21:40,324 --> 01:21:42,514
I think this is important.
If we're in time of war

1136
01:21:42,514 --> 01:21:43,973
and you want to know
what the President said

1137
01:21:43,973 --> 01:21:45,955
or what the President didn't say,
whether it's accurate or not,

1138
01:21:46,059 --> 01:21:47,623
and you have someone who says,
"I'm sent over there

1139
01:21:47,623 --> 01:21:51,377
"by the Vice President of the United States
and George Tenet to investigate this,"

1140
01:21:51,377 --> 01:21:54,401
and instead it turns out he was sent over
at the recommendation of his wife...

1141
01:21:55,861 --> 01:21:57,947
- There he is!
- Is it him?

1142
01:21:58,572 --> 01:22:00,241
- Mr. Wilson...
- This is private property.

1143
01:22:00,345 --> 01:22:03,369
- You're trespassing.
- Mr. Wilson, did the Vice President...

1144
01:22:03,265 --> 01:22:05,768
Please get off my property!

1145
01:22:05,663 --> 01:22:07,123
- I have no comment!
- Mr. Wilson,

1146
01:22:07,228 --> 01:22:09,105
- was the Niger trip a free holiday?
- Get off the property.

1147
01:22:09,105 --> 01:22:12,337
A boondoggle?
Have you been lying to us from the start?

1148
01:22:12,233 --> 01:22:16,196
I never lied. I didn't receive any payment.
My wife didn't send me. Now, leave.

1149
01:22:16,091 --> 01:22:18,177
- Did the taxpayers pay for your vacation...
- All of you, leave!

1150
01:22:18,177 --> 01:22:20,158
- ...Mr. Wilson?
- It wasn't a vacation.

1151
01:22:20,158 --> 01:22:22,557
It was a fact-finding mission
in the lead-up to a war.

1152
01:22:22,557 --> 01:22:23,808
- What? What?
- Are you against our troops?

1153
01:22:23,912 --> 01:22:25,268
- Get off my property!
- Are you against our troops?

1154
01:22:25,268 --> 01:22:26,832
All the way off the property!

1155
01:22:26,832 --> 01:22:28,083
Mr. Wilson, people are saying

1156
01:22:28,083 --> 01:22:30,169
that your wife doesn't actually work
for the CIA.

1157
01:22:30,169 --> 01:22:32,672
Is it true she's just a secretary?

1158
01:22:32,672 --> 01:22:33,714
Mr. Wilson, is it true that you

1159
01:22:33,819 --> 01:22:35,070
donated money to the Kerry campaign?

1160
01:22:34,966 --> 01:22:36,321
Mr. Wilson, your wife's a nobody!

1161
01:22:36,426 --> 01:22:38,303
Well, I think it's really all about the money.

1162
01:22:38,303 --> 01:22:41,640
We're talking about a third-rate CIA agent

1163
01:22:41,848 --> 01:22:44,559
who had a government salary,
and now she's out.

1164
01:22:44,559 --> 01:22:47,166
She could have transferred somewhere else
within the CIA.

1165
01:22:47,166 --> 01:22:50,190
She didn't have to leave.
Probably the CIA wanted her to leave

1166
01:22:50,190 --> 01:22:53,840
because she had already been in the press
without their permission.

1167
01:22:53,736 --> 01:22:58,324
It's come out that she was considered
kind of a mediocre agent at best.

1168
01:23:15,843 --> 01:23:18,137
Can I just take this pillow?

1169
01:23:26,167 --> 01:23:30,755
When we were at The Farm
training to be field officers,

1170
01:23:33,049 --> 01:23:37,012
they picked out four or five of us
and told us we stood out.

1171
01:23:37,846 --> 01:23:41,496
We were bound, hooded,
thrown into separate cells.

1172
01:23:45,354 --> 01:23:47,439
They deprived us of sleep,

1173
01:23:48,065 --> 01:23:49,316
beat us.

1174
01:23:50,046 --> 01:23:53,905
All we had to do was give up the name
of one of the others.

1175
01:23:54,843 --> 01:23:56,824
Just one name.

1176
01:23:59,744 --> 01:24:02,768
They push you until they find it.

1177
01:24:05,271 --> 01:24:07,252
Until they find the point at which you break.

1178
01:24:09,546 --> 01:24:13,613
And one by one, everybody broke

1179
01:24:15,178 --> 01:24:16,637
except me.

1180
01:24:18,306 --> 01:24:20,704
And that made me feel special.

1181
01:24:23,311 --> 01:24:25,084
You can't break me.

1182
01:24:27,795 --> 01:24:30,402
I don't have a breaking point.

1183
01:24:36,242 --> 01:24:37,702
I was wrong.

1184
01:25:18,787 --> 01:25:21,082
I'm gonna walk down the stairs
because I can't run down them.

1185
01:25:21,082 --> 01:25:24,314
Okay. You go safely,
but, let's go. Quickly.

1186
01:25:24,210 --> 01:25:26,191
Don't forget your jacket. Trevor.

1187
01:25:27,443 --> 01:25:29,111
Okay, say goodbye to your father.

1188
01:25:29,111 --> 01:25:32,344
- Hey, guys.
- We're going on a mystery tour!

1189
01:25:32,239 --> 01:25:37,453
I know you are. Come here. Come here.
I'm going to see you both real soon.

1190
01:25:38,288 --> 01:25:40,269
Why aren't you coming, Daddy?

1191
01:25:40,269 --> 01:25:44,753
- I'm going to see you really soon.
- Okay, let's get in the car, guys.

1192
01:25:45,796 --> 01:25:46,838
You got it?

1193
01:25:55,181 --> 01:25:57,683
Come on, let's go, guys.

1194
01:25:57,996 --> 01:25:59,248
Okay.

1195
01:26:06,130 --> 01:26:08,007
I'm getting soaked!

1196
01:26:22,710 --> 01:26:23,962
- Grandma!
- Grandma.

1197
01:26:24,066 --> 01:26:26,256
- Hi, baby. Hi.
- Hello, Mom.

1198
01:26:26,256 --> 01:26:28,237
Hi, baby, how are you?

1199
01:26:28,237 --> 01:26:32,617
Hey, Trevor, my goodness, how big you are!
Come on in.

1200
01:26:35,015 --> 01:26:37,205
Okay, now do you want
a red one or a green one?

1201
01:26:37,205 --> 01:26:38,665
- Red one!
- Okay.

1202
01:26:38,769 --> 01:26:41,168
- Red one!
- Here's a red one and...

1203
01:26:41,063 --> 01:26:45,964
- Apple?
- Apple and caramels, I think.

1204
01:26:45,964 --> 01:26:48,050
So, what color apple do you want?

1205
01:26:47,946 --> 01:26:49,093
- Red.
- Okay.

1206
01:26:49,093 --> 01:26:52,638
- Green.
- You want a green? Oh, good. I'm glad.

1207
01:27:20,898 --> 01:27:22,983
Afghanistan could quickly revert back to...

1208
01:27:22,879 --> 01:27:25,486
The governments of Niger and Burkina Faso

1209
01:27:25,486 --> 01:27:28,823
are interested in exploiting the
gold reserves along their common border.

1210
01:27:29,136 --> 01:27:31,951
There's not a lot of interest,
as gold's at $150 an ounce.

1211
01:27:35,914 --> 01:27:39,459
But it would compliment your holdings
in East Africa and the concession's cheap.

1212
01:27:42,171 --> 01:27:43,422
My friend.

1213
01:27:46,446 --> 01:27:48,636
- Joe Wilson.
- Karl Moleo Guderron.

1214
01:27:48,636 --> 01:27:49,992
- Such a pleasure.
- Nice to meet you.

1215
01:27:50,096 --> 01:27:51,347
How is your wife, Joe?

1216
01:27:51,556 --> 01:27:53,641
She's fine. She's well. She's...

1217
01:27:53,850 --> 01:27:58,647
Excuse me? Can I just... A black eye,
two shots of espresso, strong coffee.

1218
01:27:59,377 --> 01:28:01,149
I'm not very hungry.

1219
01:28:02,088 --> 01:28:03,339
How long are you in town?

1220
01:28:03,443 --> 01:28:04,486
Just a few days.

1221
01:28:04,486 --> 01:28:07,197
Komolea and I are excited
to hear your proposal.

1222
01:28:16,061 --> 01:28:18,355
Can I help you? Excuse me, can I help you?

1223
01:28:18,355 --> 01:28:21,067
No. I was just telling these men
that you, sir, are a fraud.

1224
01:28:21,067 --> 01:28:22,109
This is a private lunch.

1225
01:28:22,109 --> 01:28:24,821
- Could you leave now, please? Thank you.
- This man is a liar and a traitor.

1226
01:28:24,716 --> 01:28:26,698
- He is in the pay of left-wing hate groups.
- She's just a reporter.

1227
01:28:26,593 --> 01:28:28,887
He's a Democrat stooge
and he's an anti-war zealot.

1228
01:28:28,887 --> 01:28:31,599
- He has stabbed our troops in the back!
- Okay, leave now.

1229
01:28:31,599 --> 01:28:33,997
- Excuse me, I'm very sorry.
- Wilson, you've got blood on your hands

1230
01:28:33,997 --> 01:28:37,021
- and your wife is a traitor and a fantasist.
- Okay, okay, leave my table.

1231
01:28:36,917 --> 01:28:40,358
How dare you talk about my wife.
You don't know her, you don't know me.

1232
01:28:40,462 --> 01:28:42,861
- Now leave now!
- Very nice.

1233
01:28:42,757 --> 01:28:44,112
- You gentlemen should know...
- She's gonna leave.

1234
01:28:44,112 --> 01:28:46,198
- ...you're having lunch with a traitor!
- I think we should leave.

1235
01:28:46,198 --> 01:28:47,553
- Please, don't.
- No, we should.

1236
01:28:47,658 --> 01:28:50,160
- Did you hear the way that this man just...
- Shame on you.

1237
01:28:50,160 --> 01:28:51,620
You call yourself a reporter?

1238
01:28:51,829 --> 01:28:54,853
Shame on you!
You're nothing but a self-promoting hack!

1239
01:28:55,166 --> 01:28:56,313
Bitch.

1240
01:29:04,342 --> 01:29:05,489
Taxi!

1241
01:29:07,783 --> 01:29:09,869
Palisades.

1242
01:29:14,353 --> 01:29:16,543
- You okay?
- I'm fine.

1243
01:29:18,837 --> 01:29:21,444
You're him. I see you on TV.

1244
01:29:21,444 --> 01:29:23,842
- You're Joe Wilson.
- No, I'm not.

1245
01:29:23,842 --> 01:29:27,075
- Yes, brother, I see you on TV.
- That's somebody else.

1246
01:29:26,971 --> 01:29:29,161
No, no, I know you.

1247
01:29:29,161 --> 01:29:32,706
My name is Joe, too.
I'm from Sierra Leone. Freetown.

1248
01:29:32,706 --> 01:29:35,209
You've been there, right?
You like Freetown?

1249
01:29:35,417 --> 01:29:38,128
Joe, you and I both know
Freetown's a shithole.

1250
01:29:38,128 --> 01:29:39,380
That's the truth.

1251
01:29:39,693 --> 01:29:44,177
That's the truth right there, brother.
Yes, indeed, Sierra Leone is dying.

1252
01:29:44,594 --> 01:29:47,931
There's too much injustice
and corruption in Sierra Leone.

1253
01:29:47,931 --> 01:29:51,580
People at the top have too much power,
way too much power.

1254
01:29:51,685 --> 01:29:53,979
But people can't see that from over here.

1255
01:29:53,979 --> 01:29:57,211
Over here, in America, it's a different world.

1256
01:29:57,420 --> 01:30:00,236
- I wouldn't be so sure of that.
- How can you say that?

1257
01:30:00,236 --> 01:30:02,008
Land of the free, brother, home of the brave.

1258
01:30:02,634 --> 01:30:06,597
Joe, could you pull over? I'm just gonna...
Pull over here, I'm gonna walk.

1259
01:30:14,730 --> 01:30:16,399
Keep the change.

1260
01:30:29,225 --> 01:30:31,415
- That's cheating!
- I got it!

1261
01:30:35,690 --> 01:30:36,837
Ready?

1262
01:30:37,046 --> 01:30:40,174
Above your head! Above your head!
Swing your rope!

1263
01:30:40,070 --> 01:30:41,321
How is he?

1264
01:30:41,947 --> 01:30:44,345
He's okay. He's better.

1265
01:30:44,345 --> 01:30:46,118
He's shaking through.

1266
01:30:54,878 --> 01:30:56,442
I win.

1267
01:31:02,177 --> 01:31:03,428
There. There they are.

1268
01:31:03,428 --> 01:31:05,410
Do you see those guys?
Those little yellow fellas?

1269
01:31:05,410 --> 01:31:07,808
- Yeah, I see them.
- See that?

1270
01:31:09,789 --> 01:31:13,543
There's a name for them.
I used to know the name for them.

1271
01:31:14,378 --> 01:31:17,715
Some kind of... They're beautiful.

1272
01:31:28,977 --> 01:31:31,479
I think my marriage is over, Dad.

1273
01:31:44,827 --> 01:31:50,145
I know my little gal doesn't say anything
until she absolutely has to.

1274
01:31:58,592 --> 01:32:02,242
There's going to be
another Congressional Investigation.

1275
01:32:02,659 --> 01:32:05,891
He wants me to speak out.
Go on the record.

1276
01:32:09,958 --> 01:32:13,295
Like that would suddenly make
all of this go away.

1277
01:32:16,111 --> 01:32:18,718
We can't even speak to each other.

1278
01:32:18,822 --> 01:32:21,325
I can remember
saying exactly the same thing.

1279
01:32:22,055 --> 01:32:25,704
July, '72.
Me and your mom weren't getting along,

1280
01:32:25,600 --> 01:32:27,164
we were fighting all the time.

1281
01:32:27,477 --> 01:32:31,231
I guess she just plain had enough
of moving house.

1282
01:32:36,445 --> 01:32:39,365
It wasn't until I retired,
25 years in the Air Force,

1283
01:32:39,260 --> 01:32:41,450
that I realized
that we never did have a home.

1284
01:32:43,536 --> 01:32:47,290
We must have moved 20 different times,
I don't know.

1285
01:32:47,498 --> 01:32:50,835
Germany. Singapore. Australia. England.

1286
01:32:54,381 --> 01:32:58,448
You had 20 different chances
to introduce yourself as someone new.

1287
01:32:58,969 --> 01:33:03,245
You turned out all right, though. Okay.
I mean, you're responsible.

1288
01:33:04,079 --> 01:33:06,269
A little too serious, maybe.

1289
01:33:07,624 --> 01:33:10,753
It made you tough, though, huh?
Real tough.

1290
01:33:13,151 --> 01:33:17,009
Probably tougher than me
and your mom could ever understand.

1291
01:33:19,095 --> 01:33:21,910
I just can't see how this comes around.

1292
01:33:25,039 --> 01:33:26,603
Not this time.

1293
01:33:27,750 --> 01:33:29,106
Not anymore.

1294
01:33:29,419 --> 01:33:32,338
What they did was wrong, Val.
It was just plain wrong.

1295
01:33:32,338 --> 01:33:34,528
Don't you ever forget that.

1296
01:33:36,092 --> 01:33:39,221
You know, say if through some miracle
you get through this thing,

1297
01:33:39,116 --> 01:33:42,558
I mean, there's no guarantee
you and Joe won't fight.

1298
01:33:42,870 --> 01:33:44,852
You know, he's a stubborn son of a bitch.

1299
01:33:44,852 --> 01:33:48,502
I mean, he's not going to give up
any more than you are.

1300
01:33:51,421 --> 01:33:52,985
Grandpa, look.

1301
01:33:54,341 --> 01:33:57,261
I swear to God she's going to
keep at that thing until she licks it.

1302
01:33:57,261 --> 01:33:59,451
Come on, raise your hand up!

1303
01:33:59,451 --> 01:34:00,911
There you go!

1304
01:34:01,745 --> 01:34:04,978
- Good shot.
- I'm going to do it again!

1305
01:34:05,812 --> 01:34:06,959
Yeah.

1306
01:34:07,584 --> 01:34:09,149
Good try!

1307
01:34:12,798 --> 01:34:13,841
...maybe the final results.

1308
01:34:13,945 --> 01:34:14,988
Shit. Mom?

1309
01:34:14,988 --> 01:34:17,595
And it's turned out to be bad news
for one member of the White House team,

1310
01:34:17,595 --> 01:34:21,036
and a central figure he is,
Scooter Libby. Five counts.

1311
01:34:21,036 --> 01:34:25,103
And as Brian Williams just said
on NBC News, in that special report,

1312
01:34:24,999 --> 01:34:26,980
30 years he faces right now.

1313
01:34:26,980 --> 01:34:29,587
And I want to talk right now
to Dan Abrams, my colleague,

1314
01:34:29,483 --> 01:34:30,630
who handles these legal matters...

1315
01:34:30,630 --> 01:34:32,924
You can imagine
that the letter of resignation

1316
01:34:32,820 --> 01:34:36,053
was probably drafted
somewhat in advance

1317
01:34:35,948 --> 01:34:40,015
and that there were indications in the past...

1318
01:34:40,015 --> 01:34:43,456
What is next?
Lawyers for Lewis Scooter Libby

1319
01:34:43,456 --> 01:34:45,750
are preparing his defense
following his indictment on Friday.

1320
01:34:46,793 --> 01:34:49,922
Meanwhile, President Bush
is set to announce his next nominee

1321
01:34:49,922 --> 01:34:53,988
to replace Sandra Day O'Connor
on the Supreme Court.

1322
01:34:53,884 --> 01:34:56,074
Karl Rove escaped indictment today,

1323
01:34:56,074 --> 01:35:00,245
but according to sources
still faces a possible perjury charge.

1324
01:35:00,245 --> 01:35:01,914
Now, two things here.

1325
01:35:01,914 --> 01:35:06,189
First of all,
the Karl Rove business about today,

1326
01:35:05,981 --> 01:35:08,170
the fact that he was not indicted today

1327
01:35:08,170 --> 01:35:11,403
is certainly
what you would call interim good news,

1328
01:35:11,299 --> 01:35:13,593
but it can only be called interim good news

1329
01:35:13,593 --> 01:35:19,432
because as you know, the investigation,
insofar as he is concerned, is going to...

1330
01:35:49,465 --> 01:35:53,219
They served up Scooter Libby.
He's going to take the fall.

1331
01:35:55,930 --> 01:35:57,598
I'm sure they've already brokered a deal.

1332
01:35:57,598 --> 01:36:01,665
He takes the fall, the deck is stacked,
he gets pardoned.

1333
01:36:01,561 --> 01:36:04,064
I bet there won't even be a trial.

1334
01:36:17,099 --> 01:36:21,895
I don't care what they say about us.

1335
01:36:22,730 --> 01:36:26,171
I don't care how angry you get.

1336
01:36:26,588 --> 01:36:29,612
If they take all of this away, I don't care.

1337
01:36:30,655 --> 01:36:35,139
They do not get to take my marriage.

1338
01:36:40,248 --> 01:36:41,395
I'm so sorry.

1339
01:36:43,481 --> 01:36:45,045
You did good.

1340
01:36:47,027 --> 01:36:48,382
I did it for me.

1341
01:36:49,216 --> 01:36:51,198
I know why you did it.

1342
01:36:53,179 --> 01:36:54,535
Thank you.

1343
01:37:01,521 --> 01:37:04,024
If I could give it back to you...

1344
01:37:05,797 --> 01:37:09,551
If I could give you back who you were...

1345
01:37:14,348 --> 01:37:16,016
This is who I am.

1346
01:37:17,893 --> 01:37:19,353
Right here.

1347
01:37:39,687 --> 01:37:41,669
Are you ready to fight?

1348
01:37:45,527 --> 01:37:46,674
Good.

1349
01:37:48,030 --> 01:37:49,698
How many of you know the 16 words

1350
01:37:50,637 --> 01:37:54,391
in President Bush's State of the Union
address that led us to war?

1351
01:37:56,268 --> 01:37:58,875
How many know my wife's name?

1352
01:37:58,875 --> 01:38:00,439
- Valerie Plame.
- Valerie Plame.

1353
01:38:00,439 --> 01:38:04,506
Now, how can you know one
and not the other?

1354
01:38:04,506 --> 01:38:09,198
When did the question move
from "Why are we going to war?"

1355
01:38:10,032 --> 01:38:12,014
to "Who is this man's wife?"

1356
01:38:12,326 --> 01:38:17,019
I asked the first question,
but somebody else asked the second.

1357
01:38:17,019 --> 01:38:18,583
And it worked.

1358
01:38:18,583 --> 01:38:21,086
Because none of us know the truth.

1359
01:38:21,920 --> 01:38:25,883
The offense that was committed
was not committed against me,

1360
01:38:25,778 --> 01:38:28,281
it was not committed against my wife.

1361
01:38:28,281 --> 01:38:30,471
It was committed against you.

1362
01:38:30,784 --> 01:38:32,452
All of you.

1363
01:38:32,348 --> 01:38:36,415
Now, if that makes you angry
or feel misrepresented,

1364
01:38:36,832 --> 01:38:38,500
do something about it.

1365
01:38:39,647 --> 01:38:42,984
When Benjamin Franklin
left Independence Hall

1366
01:38:42,984 --> 01:38:45,174
just after the second drafting,

1367
01:38:45,174 --> 01:38:47,051
he was approached by a woman
on the street.

1368
01:38:47,051 --> 01:38:49,554
The woman said, "Mr. Franklin,

1369
01:38:49,554 --> 01:38:52,995
"what manner of government
have you bequeathed us?"

1370
01:38:52,995 --> 01:38:56,228
And Franklin said, "A Republic, madam.

1371
01:38:57,271 --> 01:38:58,522
"If you can keep it."

1372
01:38:58,939 --> 01:39:02,276
The responsibility of a country

1373
01:39:02,172 --> 01:39:05,717
is not in the hands of a privileged few.

1374
01:39:06,239 --> 01:39:10,305
We are strong, and we are free from tyranny

1375
01:39:10,305 --> 01:39:16,249
as long as each one of us
remembers his or her duty as a citizen.

1376
01:39:16,041 --> 01:39:19,690
Whether it's to report a pothole
at the top of your street

1377
01:39:19,586 --> 01:39:21,880
or lies in a State of the Union address,

1378
01:39:21,880 --> 01:39:24,904
speak out! Ask those questions.

1379
01:39:24,904 --> 01:39:26,677
Demand that truth.

1380
01:39:27,199 --> 01:39:29,701
Democracy is not a free ride, man.

1381
01:39:29,597 --> 01:39:31,578
I'm here to tell you.

1382
01:39:31,578 --> 01:39:34,185
But, this is where we live.

1383
01:39:34,811 --> 01:39:40,233
And if we do our job,
this is where our children will live.

1384
01:39:41,589 --> 01:39:43,362
God bless America.

1385
01:39:49,201 --> 01:39:51,704
Ms. Wilson,
we're pleased to have you here.

1386
01:39:51,600 --> 01:39:55,041
Thank you very much
for coming to our committee today.

1387
01:39:54,937 --> 01:39:59,733
It's the practice of this committee
that all witnesses are administered an oath.

1388
01:39:59,942 --> 01:40:03,175
And I'd like to ask you to stand
and raise your right hand.

1389
01:40:03,592 --> 01:40:06,512
Do you promise to tell the truth
and nothing but the truth?

1390
01:40:06,929 --> 01:40:08,180
- I do.
- Please be seated.

1391
01:40:11,934 --> 01:40:13,811
Now, there's a button
on the base of the mike.

1392
01:40:13,707 --> 01:40:16,522
Be sure to press it in
and pull it closely enough to you

1393
01:40:16,522 --> 01:40:18,504
so you can be heard.

1394
01:40:26,116 --> 01:40:29,766
Good morning, Mr. Chairman
and members of the committee.

1395
01:40:31,330 --> 01:40:33,728
My name is Valerie Plame Wilson.

1396
01:40:35,814 --> 01:40:39,568
And I'm honored to have been invited
to testify under oath

1397
01:40:40,402 --> 01:40:43,531
before the Committee on Oversight
and Government Reform

1398
01:40:43,531 --> 01:40:47,076
on the critical issue
of safeguarding classified information.

1399
01:40:48,223 --> 01:40:52,186
I'm grateful for this opportunity
to set the record straight.

1400
01:40:53,437 --> 01:40:57,504
I served the United States loyally
and to the best of my ability

1401
01:40:57,400 --> 01:41:01,988
as a covert operations officer
for the Central Intelligence Agency.

1402
01:41:02,926 --> 01:41:06,576
I worked on behalf of the national security
of our country,

1403
01:41:06,472 --> 01:41:09,392
on behalf of the people of the United States,

1404
01:41:09,287 --> 01:41:13,876
until my name and true affiliations
were exposed in the national media

1405
01:41:13,876 --> 01:41:19,194
on July 14th, 2003, after a leak
by administration officials.

1406
01:41:20,132 --> 01:41:23,156
Today, I can tell this committee even more.

1407
01:41:23,991 --> 01:41:26,598
In the run-up to the war with Iraq,

1408
01:41:26,598 --> 01:41:30,247
I worked in the counter-proliferation
division of the CIA,

1409
01:41:30,247 --> 01:41:35,357
still as a covert officer whose affiliation
with the CIA was classified.

1410
01:41:35,983 --> 01:41:40,362
I raced to discover solid intelligence
for senior policymakers

1411
01:41:40,362 --> 01:41:44,012
on Iraq's presumed weapons
of mass destruction programs.

1412
01:41:44,638 --> 01:41:48,809
While I helped to manage
and run secret world-wide operations

1413
01:41:48,600 --> 01:41:53,606
against this WMD target
from CIA headquarters in Washington,

1414
01:41:53,397 --> 01:41:58,924
I also traveled to foreign countries
on secret missions

1415
01:41:58,820 --> 01:42:01,010
to find vital intelligence.

1416
01:42:01,531 --> 01:42:04,764
I loved my career
because I love my country.

1417
01:42:04,764 --> 01:42:07,266
I was proud of the serious responsibilities

1418
01:42:07,371 --> 01:42:11,125
entrusted to me
as a CIA covert operations officer.
